t to the mob area so if they go oom they die so they will have mana to heal again.  Very goofy, not a real strategy, and more of a zergling rush approach, but nonetheless, the only approach.<P>Aladain<P></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Astur</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">There were actually several things that pissed us all off.<P><b>1.</b> Donal's BP nerf as mentioned.<BR><b>2.</b> PoG/Velious Quest BP nerf. Celestial Elixer was totally removed as the effect and MoK was added. Even though it was an unstackable effect that already had a 30sec casting time!<BR><b>3.</b> Healing Aggro went <b>WAY</b> up. They subsequently lowered it some, but it's still f'd up. If you CH on a pull (which you have to do on a lot of raids) you pretty much guaranteed yourself a sacrificed cleric.<P>------------------<BR>Astur il'Ayan, Cleric of Brell<BR>Dealers of Death on Solusek Ro<BR>Profile  <A HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=50334" TARGET=_blank>http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=50334</A></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Dikmer</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Wasn't there also a BP that could be rightclicked from inventory that gave invis, then nerfed so you had to wear it to get the effect, thereby disallowing it's use by clerics?</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">kitsinu</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Yeah, you now have to wear the breastplate to activate it.  It was a very rare item in the first place also.  Something to aspire to own.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Snorfen</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">the BIG nerf was the healing agro nerf.<P>the BP things are a pain but dont hit many clerics. The healing agro changes hit all clerics 39+<P>changing the healing agro meant 2 things:<P>a cleric dies more<BR>a raid gets wiped out more often<P>= more downtime for everyone.<P>it especially sucks since it has nothing to do with risk vs reward... <P>if a wiz nukes the whatsit out of a mob and gets agroed he gains:<P>1) mob is lower health <BR>2) fair chance to get exp and loot<P>if a cleric complete heales a warrior he gains:<P>1) agro from the mob and usually (if he survives) can heal himself after.<P>In my opinion verant would need to do one important thing:<P>let heals count for the exp gain too, so not only most damage done but also most damage healed REWARD you for the RISK you take.<P>of course this would also end any powerleveling... and oh my i can hear the moaning chorus.<P>snorfen<BR></FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Gello</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">An interesting thing about the incarnadine bp.  Until recently I was under the assumption that any effect you can activate from inventory isn't limited by class/race/diety.  But the staff of the temperate flux and the circlet of shadows are.  (Imagine my joy when I found out necs were using the circlet from inventory--and the disappointment when I couldn't.)  Interesting that they didn't just do this for the bp, instead of changing it so it had to be worn.<P>I've no opinion on the nerfs.  Aside from the Great Muffin Nerf of '01, none has really affected me.</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Meddik</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I donno.<P>There was also the MoK nerf, that really stank.<P>But my personal least favorite nerf was when Alcohol started lowering wisdom.<P>------------------<BR>Meddik Sawbones<BR>Member of <A HREF="http://www.suvangi.com/drunkenbandits/" TARGET=_blank>Drunken Bandits</A><BR>(Bristlebane Server)</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#dedfdf"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Aean</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I think alot of the outrage from these nerfs didn't come from the actual nerfs themselves but the way in which verant handled them. very unproffesional. Plus the fact that it was like 5 nerfs in a row while everyone else was getting things added to their classes. <P>I'm still waiting for those class changes to clerics, they kinda stopped after rangers and druids:P</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#f7f7f7"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Boanerges</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Should also note that when they said they were working on a new effect for the BP, we asked for Aegis or Aegolism (Aegis seemed more likely) but they put MoK on it instead. As if that weren't bad enough, paladins get Shield of Words on their BPs. Talk about insulting. We're a buffing class and yet our hybrid gets a manaless buff we have to cough up 300 mana for.<P>------------------<BR>Boanerges Thundercry<BR>Erudite Templar of Prexus<BR>Cohort Chalybeius<BR>Cazic Thule Server</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
